Against this backdrop, the United Nations Children's Fund, together with the country's department of health held a round table discussion on Tuesday, to tackle the nation's breastfeeding challenge. 

Speakers at the event held in Johannesburg focused on supporting breastfeeding in the workplace, one area where concerted effort is needed. 

One of the participants was a lecturer from Stellenbosch University, Lynnete Daniels who presented preliminary findings of a research on workplace breastfeeding, which indicate that many nursing moms are still not supported by their employers.. --ChannelAfrica--